<plot>Journey down river to the Amazonian Rainforest in this powerful and timely documentary. International energy companies - with the blessing of Washington D.C. - have come to the Peruvian Rainforest to exploit a natural gas field. To the people of the lower Urubamba river basin, this is the only land they have ever known. To the energy-hungry multinational interests, this land is a series of blocks on a development map. When a society from the past meets the present, can it still have a future?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?075000</url></doc>
